  "text": "I implemented a minimal Envoy HTTP filter following the established extension patterns found in the envoyproxy/envoy v1.31.2 repository. The implementation consists of three key files:\n\n1. **pass_through_filter.h**: Defines the PassThroughFilter class that inherits from Http::StreamDecoderFilter (as defined in envoy/http/filter.h). The class follows the pattern established in source/extensions/filters/http/common/pass_through_filter.h and implements the required virtual methods: decodeHeaders, decodeData, and decodeTrailers, each returning Continue status to allow data to pass through without modification. The filter also implements setDecoderFilterCallbacks and onDestroy methods as specified by the StreamFilterBase interface.\n\n2. **pass_through_filter.cc**: Provides the implementation of the filter methods. Each decode method simply returns the appropriate Continue status (FilterHeadersStatus::Continue, FilterDataStatus::Continue, FilterTrailersStatus::Continue), following the pattern observed in source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/buffer_filter.cc. The setDecoderFilterCallbacks method stores a reference to the callbacks as seen in other filters.\n\n3. **config.cc**: Implements the factory registration using the NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory pattern from source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h. The PassThroughFilterConfigFactory class provides the createFilterFactoryFromProto method that returns a FilterFactoryCb lambda, following the exact pattern used in source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/config.cc. The filter is registered using the REGISTER_FACTORY macro with the name 'envoy.filters.http.pass_through'.\n\nThe implementation follows the same extension architecture pattern used throughout Envoy's HTTP filter system, particularly mirroring the structure of the buffer filter found in source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/. The filter inherits from Http::StreamDecoderFilter as required and implements all necessary methods to integrate with Envoy's filter chain architecture."
}

